title: Mass-spectrometric measurements of 3H, 3He, and 4He produced in thermal- neutron ternary fission of 235U: evidence for short-range 4He

x4freetext: The thick catcher Pb foils, 30 mg/cm2
thick, were placed together to give a total thickness
of 330 mg/cm2, sufficient to stop normally incident
alpha particles of 40 MeV and tritons of 14 MeV.
In order to detect possible short-range components of
the light particles, stacks of Pb foils were arranged
in such a way that He contents could be measured for
Helium and fission-product Kr were extracted from the
Pb foils by vaporizing these in a vacuum. 3H was
removed completely by the use of titanium sponge at
Calibration of the mass spectrometer for peak-height
response and mass discrimination was achieved by
analyzing atmospheric He prepared from aliquots of air
of known volume introduced immediately after each
The number of fissions in each sample was determined by
absolute measurements of the fission 86Kr content.
tenths of 1 mg were prepared by evaporation of weak
uranyl nitrate solution onto Pb foil.
